"    Malignant and benign gastric ulcer as seen on upper gastrointestinal (UGI) series",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 583px; height: 312px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Upper GI series showing the differences between a malignant and benign gastric ulcer.",
"    <br/>",
"    (A) Malignant gastric ulcer of the distal lesser curvature. There is the biconvex meniscus sign with a nodular ulcer mound (arrow).",
"    <br/>",
"    (B) Benign gastric ulcer of the lesser curvature. The ulcer crater has smooth margins and projects beyond the gastric wall (arrow).",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"     Courtesy of Paul C Schroy, III, MD.",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
